WEBVTT

00:11.497 --> 00:15.232
Can you tell me about the day
that Mo Williams was murdered?

00:15.531 --> 00:17.118
Well, first,
I heard the gunshot.

00:17.119 --> 00:18.140
And what did you do?

00:18.141 --> 00:19.394
I looked out my peephole

00:19.395 --> 00:21.921
and I saw Hiram Diaz
standing in front of Mo.

00:21.923 --> 00:23.155
And there was another
dude out there, too,

00:23.157 --> 00:24.724
but I couldn't
see his face.

00:24.726 --> 00:25.925
What was Mr. Diaz doing?

00:25.927 --> 00:27.994
You want me to say
he was holding a gun, right?

00:27.996 --> 00:30.329
Miranda, I told you, I just
want you to tell the truth.

00:30.331 --> 00:32.765
He shot Mo in the chest
with a .38.

00:32.767 --> 00:35.734
How did you know
the gun was a .38?

00:35.736 --> 00:37.202
'Cause I got the same gun.

00:37.204 --> 00:39.938
Do you have a permit for that?

00:39.940 --> 00:42.041
Come 8:00 at night, Hiram and
the rest of the Double Treys

00:42.043 --> 00:43.509
shut the elevators down.

00:43.511 --> 00:46.078
They deal crack right out in the
open like they delivering pizza.

00:46.080 --> 00:48.914
You gonna stand there and tell
me you wouldn't carry a gun too,

00:48.916 --> 00:51.750
Miss It Ain't Like That
On Park Avenue?

00:51.752 --> 00:52.984
One, I don't live
on Park Avenue.

00:52.986 --> 00:55.020
Two, you announce that
in open court,

00:55.022 --> 00:58.289
you will be arrested for
criminal possession of a weapon.

00:58.291 --> 01:00.458
Okay, I'm gonna shut up now.

01:00.460 --> 01:01.760
Why don't we take a break

01:01.762 --> 01:03.562
and finish this
when we all come back.

01:03.564 --> 01:05.296
Good, I'm starving.

01:10.303 --> 01:13.037
Will you go back to the scene
and find me something--

01:13.039 --> 01:15.373
and I mean anything--
because her testimony

01:15.375 --> 01:17.608
is not gonna be enough
to convict Diaz.

01:17.610 --> 01:19.610
You think?

01:23.950 --> 01:25.215
Sir.

01:25.217 --> 01:26.917
How you feeling, Baker?

01:26.919 --> 01:28.518
I'm fine, sir.

01:30.122 --> 01:32.022
Why are you
lurking by the elevator?

01:32.024 --> 01:33.256
I'm not lurking.
You lurking

01:33.258 --> 01:36.193
always means bad news
or a plea to keep my mouth shut.

01:36.195 --> 01:39.429
Mr. Lewis from the attorney
general's office is here, sir.

01:40.299 --> 01:41.631
He's already here?

01:44.303 --> 01:45.535
Where?

01:45.537 --> 01:46.803
Waiting in your office.

01:46.805 --> 01:49.806
He needed to speak to the
governor and wanted a hard line.

01:51.610 --> 01:53.276
From my office?

01:53.278 --> 01:54.677
Since when do we do that?

01:54.679 --> 01:56.646
We extended the courtesy.

01:56.648 --> 01:57.914
We?

02:01.219 --> 02:03.086
No problem.
I'll make sure

02:03.088 --> 02:05.021
he's aware that's on
the table as well.

02:05.023 --> 02:06.422
I'm gonna get into
it with him now.

02:06.424 --> 02:08.424
If that's the governor,
say hey for me.

02:08.425 --> 02:10.994
He just stepped in;
he sends his best.

02:10.996 --> 02:13.329
Okay, I'll call you after.

02:13.331 --> 02:14.696
Commissioner.

02:14.698 --> 02:18.601
If you need to make another
phone call, I can wait outside.

02:18.603 --> 02:20.636
No. No, no, no,
no. But, um...

02:20.638 --> 02:22.838
just us, please.

02:22.840 --> 02:24.840
He stays.

02:26.210 --> 02:28.410
So?
Thank you for seeing me.

02:28.412 --> 02:31.013
You're welcome.
I'm here as a courtesy.

02:31.015 --> 02:33.314
Holding the door is a courtesy;
letting you in here

02:33.316 --> 02:34.850
to use my phone,
that's a courtesy;

02:34.852 --> 02:36.351
but launching
another investigation

02:36.353 --> 02:40.421
into my department--
not so much.

02:41.659 --> 02:42.918
What he means is...

02:42.919 --> 02:45.093
What I mean is
let's show each other

02:45.095 --> 02:48.229
the genuine courtesy
of full transparency.

02:49.599 --> 02:53.368
We are opening an investigation
into the NYPD's use of force,

02:53.370 --> 02:56.171
particularly as it pertains
to police actions

02:56.173 --> 02:58.506
in minority neighborhoods.

02:59.676 --> 03:03.044
Well, there you go.
That wasn't so hard, was it?

03:03.046 --> 03:04.945
I'd appreciate it,
as a courtesy,

03:04.947 --> 03:06.781
if you'd dial down the attitude.

03:06.783 --> 03:09.784
I am here with the full
confidence of the governor.

03:09.786 --> 03:12.586
Duly noted.

03:12.588 --> 03:16.691
This is a copy of our annual
firearms discharge report.

03:16.693 --> 03:19.859
It is a deep dive
into the use of firearms

03:19.861 --> 03:22.229
by every member
of this department

03:22.231 --> 03:24.565
and all accompanying statistics.

03:24.567 --> 03:26.099
Thank you for this.

03:26.101 --> 03:27.634
You're welcome.
But I didn't come down here

03:27.636 --> 03:29.503
to pick up papers.

03:29.505 --> 03:33.106
We'd also like your
personal cooperation on this.

03:34.042 --> 03:35.375
Why?

03:35.377 --> 03:38.745
Well, the relationship between
the police and the public

03:38.747 --> 03:41.114
is a matter of discord
across the country.

03:41.116 --> 03:43.249
Now, the governor would
like to allay any fears

03:43.251 --> 03:46.285
or misconceptions that police
shootings in New York City

03:46.287 --> 03:48.321
may have bias elements.

03:48.323 --> 03:49.589
You don't need me.
It's all in there.

03:49.591 --> 03:51.591
Go crunch the numbers.
Being part of

03:51.593 --> 03:54.126
a public investigation
into NYPD shootings

03:54.128 --> 03:56.495
and their impact
on minority communities

03:56.497 --> 03:58.264
is a win for everyone involved.

03:58.266 --> 03:59.169
How's that?

03:59.193 --> 04:00.467
We complete our
investigation,

04:00.468 --> 04:03.035
we make our recommendations
to the mayor's office,

04:03.037 --> 04:05.838
to your office,
to the city council,

04:05.840 --> 04:08.574
and we all move on.

04:10.510 --> 04:12.811
No. You move on,

04:12.813 --> 04:16.180
pleased as punch with
your thousand-page report.

04:16.183 --> 04:19.584
I, on the other hand, am left
to deal with the fallout.

04:19.586 --> 04:22.120
If it's as you say,
why would there be fallout?

04:22.123 --> 04:24.223
Because that's the way
it works, and you know it.

04:24.225 --> 04:26.924
There has to be
fault found, Robert.

04:26.926 --> 04:31.129
And fallout, for your
investigation to earn its keep.

04:39.072 --> 04:41.339
Please tell me
you have something.

04:41.341 --> 04:44.175
I got a lot of charm, Erin,
but it ain't working today.

04:44.177 --> 04:46.644
Everyone's just too scared
to testify against Diaz?

04:46.646 --> 04:49.446
I wish. More like they're
too scared to talk to cops.

04:49.448 --> 04:51.149
But I got this.
What's that?

04:51.151 --> 04:53.785
The deli across from the
building has security cameras.

04:53.787 --> 04:56.788
I got what looks like Diaz
and an unidentified male

04:56.790 --> 04:58.756
leaving the premises
right after the murder.

04:58.758 --> 05:00.758
Before you get excited,

05:00.760 --> 05:02.626
it's as clear as
mud, but maybe...

05:02.628 --> 05:04.261
What the hell's going on here?

05:04.263 --> 05:05.239
Excuse me?

05:05.263 --> 05:06.298
What are you talking
about, Danny?

05:06.299 --> 05:08.231
Why the hell's
he poking around my case?

05:08.233 --> 05:09.433
It's a D.A.'s

05:09.435 --> 05:10.467
office case now.
Hey, I'm not

05:10.469 --> 05:11.902
talking to you,
I'm talking to her.

05:11.904 --> 05:14.405
You poach my case and you
don't even give me a heads up?

05:14.407 --> 05:16.406
I don't work for you!

05:16.408 --> 05:18.108
I don't give a damn
who you work for!

05:18.110 --> 05:19.575
You don't
cherry-pick my cases!

05:19.577 --> 05:22.212
Okay, guys,
both of you, stop it.

05:22.214 --> 05:23.646
I handed you an eyewitness.

05:23.648 --> 05:25.315
Do you know how difficult
that is in that neighborhood?

05:25.317 --> 05:27.784
And if I was trying this case
in Staten Island,

05:27.786 --> 05:29.385
I might get a conviction.

05:29.387 --> 05:31.188
But there is no way
that witness

05:31.190 --> 05:33.189
is going to sway
12 Manhattan jurors.

05:33.191 --> 05:34.791
Well, maybe you
should've asked me.

05:34.793 --> 05:37.927
Well, she asked me.
Same credentials as you.

05:37.929 --> 05:39.430
Good, then go find
your own case.

05:39.454 --> 05:40.331
I've got a guy

05:40.332 --> 05:41.798
who's gotten away with
a half dozen murders

05:41.800 --> 05:43.098
finally on trial.

05:43.100 --> 05:45.568
I'm not gonna lose it
because of your two egos.

05:45.570 --> 05:48.804
Now, my witness hasn't
answered a cell, a text

05:48.806 --> 05:51.373
or a e-mail--
nothing since she left here.

05:51.375 --> 05:54.143
Go find her and bring her back.

